Course Name: Certificate Course in IT Infrastructure & System Administration
Duration: 6-8 Months

Module-1:Digital Office Productivity & Collaboration Tools
(Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Email, Cloud & Team Collaboration)


Module-2: PC Hardware, Diagnostics & System Maintenance
(Computer Components, Assembly, Troubleshooting, Preventive Maintenance & System Health)

Module-3: Computer Networking Foundations & Connectivity Essentials:
(Networking Basics, LAN/WAN Concepts, Devices, IP Addressing & Connectivity)


Module-4: Client Operating Systems: Windows 10 /11 Administration 
(Installation, Configuration, User Management, Security & Troubleshooting)


Module-5: Enterprise Windows Server Administration (Server 2019 / 2022) 
(Active Directory, Users/Group, Domains, DNS, DHCP, Group Policy, File Services & Security)

Module-6: Enterprise Linux System Administration (Redhat 8/9)
(System Installation, Users & Permissions, Services, Networking & Security)


Course Name:Professional Cyber Security Programs:

•	Cyber Security Foundations & Threat Intelligence
(Understand cyber threats, attack vectors, and security fundamentals)
Duration – 15 Days

•	Network Security, Firewalls & Perimeter Défense
(Secure enterprise networks against internal and external attacks)
Duration – 1 Month

•	Linux Security & Open-Source Security Operations
(Master Linux administration from a cyber security perspective)
Duration – 1 Month

•	Windows & Active Directory Security Engineering
(Secure enterprise Windows domains and enterprise environments)
Duration – 1 Month

•	Ethical Hacking & Penetration Testing Essentials
(Learn legal ethical hacking techniques using structured methodologies)
Duration – 2-3 Month


•	Web Application Security & OWASP Top 10
(Identify, exploit, and remediate real-world web vulnerabilities)
Duration – 1-2 Month

•	Vulnerability Assessment & Penetration Testing (VAPT)
(Assess risk, perform audits, and deliver professional security reports)
Duration – 1-2 Month

•	Bug Bounty Hunting & Responsible Disclosure Practices
(Find real-world vulnerabilities and report them ethically to organizations)
Duration – 1-2 Month

•	Security Operations Center (SOC) & SIEM Monitoring
(Detect, analyse, and respond to live security incidents)
Duration – 1-2 Month

•	Digital Forensics & Incident Response (DFIR)
(Investigate cyber-attacks and handle security breaches professionally)
Duration – 1-2 Month

•	Cloud Security Fundamentals & Zero-Trust Architecture
(Secure cloud, hybrid, and modern enterprise environments)
Duration – 1-Month

•	Linux Shell Scripting for Cyber Security & Automation
(Learn Linux shell scripting fundamentals to automate basic cyber security and system administration tasks.)
Duration – 1-Month

Course Name:Professional Cloud & Virtualization Programs:
Data Center Architecture & Design
(Understand modern data centre architecture, components, power, cooling, and high-availability design concepts.)
Duration – 15 Days

Enterprise Storage Fundamentals
(Learn core storage technologies including SAN, NAS, DAS, redundancy, backup, and data protection basics.)
Duration – 15 Days


Server Virtualization with Microsoft Hyper-V
(Deploy and manage virtual machines using Microsoft Hyper-V in enterprise server environments.)
Duration – 1 Month


Enterprise Virtualization with VMware ESXi & vSphere
(Configure, manage, and optimize virtual infrastructure using VMware ESXi and vSphere technologies.)
Duration – 1 Month


Amazon Web Services (AWS) Cloud Infrastructure Fundamentals
(Build and manage core AWS cloud services including compute, storage, networking, and security basics.)
Duration – 1 Month

Microsoft Azure Cloud Infrastructure Fundamentals
(Design and operate cloud infrastructure using Microsoft Azure services and management tools.)
Duration – 1 Month

Microsoft 365 Fundamentals: Identity, Email & Collaboration 
(Administer cloud-based identity, email, and collaboration services using Microsoft 365.)
Duration – 10 Days

Basic Cloud Automation & Operations
(Automate routine cloud operations, monitoring, backups, and cost optimization using basic scripting and tools.)
Duration – 10 Days


Course Name:Software Development & Programming:
•	Website Development (Front End / Back End / Full Stack)
(Learn to design and develop complete websites—from user interface to database and deployment—using industry-relevant tools and live projects.)

•	Programming (C, C++, Java, Python)
(Build strong programming fundamentals, logic and problem-solving skills using the most in-demand languages for academics and IT careers.)

•	College Projects & Internship
(Industry-guided mini and final year projects with practical implementation, documentation, internship certification and viva support.)

•	School Syllabus
(Complete support for school computer syllabus, practical and basic coding to build strong technical foundations from an early stage.)
